defaulther
default needs.
default 
defaultThe
default cli
defaultent who was bedbound and needed a hoist to get out of bed
default,
default with carers attending four times a day to change her incontinence pads. She had dementia, neuropathy, incontinence and was unable to stand. Under the NHS funded care package, the PCT insisted that 
defaultthey could only provide 3 pads per day - not enough 
defaultfor her
default needs and they could not afford to buy any more 
defaultherself
default. The bureau advised that the care package should meet the cost of however many pads were required and wrote a complaint letter. After furthe
defaultr advocacy by the bureau including an initial application for judicial review, the NHS incontinence team re-assessed the client and agreed to allow four pads.
default Without legal aid funding for making this initial application it is much less likely they would h
defaultave been able to put this extra pressure 
defaultto get the support they needed
default.
default&#xa0;
defaultIt was only a successful judicial review that forced the government to rethink rules on the housing benefit size criteria so that severely disabled children did not have to share a r
defaultoom.
default 
defaultA family with two severely disabled children came to their local CAB because they felt the rules amounted to disability discrimination.  With support from CPAG lawyers the case was taken all the way to the court of appeal and DWP agreed to modify thei
defaultr rules. 
defaultMeaning a number of families can now afford to give better care for their disabled children.
