default&#xa0;
defaultThe current plans would affect vulnerable groups who need protection such as mothers and babies and children in custody and 
defaultremoves important issues such as treatment and prison conditions
default&#xa0;
defaultfrom scope. 
defaultThose with 
defaultmental health issues and/or learning disabilities and young offenders will find it especially hard to obtain effective redress for other serious matters. 
default&#xa0;
defaultThe prison 
defaultombudsman service does not have the power to enforce resolutions and therefore cannot
default&#xa0;
defaultalways resolve these problems without recourse to the courts, and the proposal makes no attempt to distinguish between trivial and serious complaints but rather imposes a
default blanket restriction. We believe accountability
default&#xa0;
defaultfor
default&#xa0;
defaultmistakes or
default&#xa0;
defaultmaltreatment
default&#xa0;
defaultin criminal justice system is of the highest importance but will be sacrificed if the proposal on restricting legal aid in prison law cases goes ahead.
default&#xa0;
defaultThe projected saving from 
defaultthis measure is
default&#xa0;
defaulttiny
default in Government spending terms - £4 million according to the consultation paper impact assessment - but the implications for victims of mistreatment in prison are huge
default. 
default&#xa0;
defaultCitizens Advice Bureaux run many prison based advice projects - cu
defaultrrently covering around 50 prisons, so if the government reduces legal aid funding for advice to prisoners this may well add to the pressure on our staff and volunteers currently delivering advice in prisons.  This in turn would have a damaging impact on t
defaulthe prison and parole services if we are not able to support as many clients.
